\section{Key Findings}

\begin{enumerate}
    \item \textbf{Vega-Weighted Wins Decisively}: OOS RMSE of \$0.546 is the best among all four objectives, translating to superior hedging accuracy across the entire term structure (7--112 days).

    \item \textbf{Trade-off Between Objectives}:
    \begin{itemize}
        \item \textbf{Vega-Weighted}: \$0.546 OOS RMSE (best for dollar-based P\&L hedging)
        \item \textbf{Relative}: \$0.563 OOS RMSE (best for percentage-based strategies, 3.1\% higher error)
        \item \textbf{SSE}: \$0.629 OOS RMSE (baseline; inferior to specialized objectives)
    \end{itemize}
    
    \item \textbf{Recommendation for Practice}: Use Vega-Weighted as the default objective function for production calibration. It minimizes dollar exposure across the portfolio, which is the primary concern in derivatives risk management.
\end{enumerate}

